The paper deals with the parameterized complexity of local graph partitioning problems, which are related to graph algorithms and combinatorial optimization. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves techniques related to graph theory and combinatorics, which are covered by cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Finally, the paper deals with optimization problems, which are covered by cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
